=head1 NAME

Pea?rl icons - This is a test

=head1 SYNOPSIS

=begin html

<h2>Absolute path</h2>
<img src="http://www.pthbb.org/manual/software/perl/icons/whitebg.gif"></p>

<h2>Relative path</h2>
<img src="/src/JPIERCE/RTx-CFC-0.01/share/bluebg.gif">

<h2>Inlined source</h2>
<img src="data:image/gif;base64,">

=end html

=head1 DESCRIPTION

In the beginning ActiveState neglected to include an icon in their
port of PERL. I sent them sample icons ( wpearl formerly pearl1,
gpearl formerly pearl2, and ipearl formerly pearl3; bpearl was added
later). Whether they heeded my letter or someone else's ActiveState
finally began including an icon in build 5xy. However it is a rather
unattractive one. A yellow pearl to me would denote poor quality.
Thusly I make my icons available to you in F<share/>;
my personal favorite being ipearl. Smaakelijk!

